heaviest_rainrate.status: On 02 September 2025, the rain fell at an exceptional rate, peaking at 27.0mm per hour, the heaviest downpour recorded.  A total of 21.19mm fell over the 15.0 hour storm.

summary.description:
Today, a bit warmer for the feels like temperature (up 5.3°C) and outside temperature (up 4.2°C), more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 5%), and drier conditions in rainfall (down 0.2 mm).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in cloud levels (up 322 m).

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 465 m), feels like temperature (down 2.7°C), dew point temperature (down 2.7°C), and outside temperature (down 1.7°C) when compared to today.
